        .setColumnPosition(entry.getSourceColumn() + 1);
      if (entry.getNameId() != UNMAPPED) {
        x.setIdentifier(names[entry.getNameId()]);
      }
      return x.build();
    }
  }

And the addMapping unchanged.

Now JSON output.

Make sure to use proper escaping for strings. The fixed_code array should contain the full source of each function as a JSON string.

I'll output the trigger methods with the full path. Since the test methods belong to com.google.javascript.jscomp.TypeCheckTest, the full path is that class name plus method name. For example, "com.google.javascript.jscomp.TypeCheckTest::testDuplicateStaticMethodDecl1". So list them accordingly.

